tags.description:
## MultiProject

`<multi-project>` use `projection` to project `data` and expose it under `projectedData`

attributes.name: data
attributes.description: [`data`] data with points to be projected

attributes.name: projected-data
attributes.description: [`data`] data with points to be projected

attributes.name: coordinate-accessor-path
attributes.description:
`coordinateAccessorPath` path for computing the `valueAccessor` function
a value of ´key´ will generate  an accessor function like ´function(d) {return d.key}´
a value of ´+value.count´ will generate  an accessor function like ´function(d) {return +d.value.count}´

attributes.name: coordinate-accessor
attributes.description: `coordinates` accessor function returning [x,y] coordinates from the data. Passed directly or through a coordinatePath

attributes.name: key
attributes.description: `key` the key under which projected coordinates are stored
